cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new framework for learning multifaceted features using a single-branch neural network, which involves the use of compound batch image erasing and hierarchical structured loss. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) since these areas are relevant to the proposed method.
